Raw-steel production by the nation's mills increased 2.8% last week to 1,843,000 tons from 1,793,000 tons the previous week, the American Iron and Steel Institute said. 

Last week's output fell 0.2% from the 1,846,000 tons produced a year earlier. 

The industry used 82.8% of its capability last week, compared with 80.7% the previous week and 86.1% a year ago. 

The capability utilization rate is a calculation designed to indicate at what percent of its production capability the industry is operating in a given week. 

